bug.short_desc: [All] virt-manager localized GUI partially in English

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1142436 create VM step 4
Description of problem: Some of the strings in virt-manager are displayed in English (translated in zanata)
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): virt-manager-1.3.2-3.fc24
How reproducible: run virt-manager, go through Create VM steps, or check the properties of the existing VM. Try to force reset or poweroff VM. Untranslated strings in various parts of GUI. I will attach some example screenshots but mainly it looks like the most recent translation from master branch just needs to be incorporated.
Actual results: * Step 4 of VM create: Strings in English: "Create a disk image for the virtual machine", "Select or create custom storage" (both translated in zanata)
* Configuring network interface, step 2: Strings in English: "Static", "No configuration", "No child interfaces selected"
And some others
Expected results: GUI is fully localized, latest translation from zanata is included.

Created attachment 1142437 VM force poweroff confirmation screen
VM force poweroff confirmation message partially in English. Similar applies to force reset dialog.

Created attachment 1142438 Add network interface screen
Example of network interface screen. Needs to be updated with translation in zanata.

Similar issues for Brazilian Portuguese.
A few strings are in English in the application, but were translated in zanata, such as 'format, 'size' and 'used by'.
Additional info: application doesn't reflect the latest translation from zanata. Please incorporate it to GUI.
https://fedora.zanata.org/iteration/view/virt-manager/master/languages/pt-BR

Please take latest translation for repackage. It shows translated Japanese, but the translation appears bad old translation. Newer correct translation exists in zanata but not reflected. Example1: 1. create new vm 2. at step 4/5, two options, "C_reate a disk image for the virtual machine" and "_Select or create custom storage"
"_Select or create custom storage" The translation for this string appears as "用に", bad no meaning old translation. While correct good translation of "カスタムストレージの選択または作成(_S)" has been provided in Zanata.
Example2: 1. go to Help 2. click Credit 3. it shows latest translator credit is "Shushi Kurose,2010"
"Shushi Kurose,2010", the year is 6 years old.
*** Bug 1322646 has been marked as a duplicate of this bug. ***
I've pulled latest translations from zanata into virt-manager git, they will be in fedora with the next upstream virt-manager release
